The paper deals with community detection in networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with network analysis and community detection. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper introduces a new algorithm for post-processing network partitions. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as community detection can be seen as a form of unsupervised learning. cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the CHAMP algorithm. Finally, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as the paper deals with network structures.
